# Sweet Potatoes, Bourbon

## Ingredients

2 Large Sweet Potatoes
Olive Oil
Chinese Five Spice

1 Stick Butter, unsalted
10 Sage Leaves, fresh

1 Cup Brown Sugar
1/2 Cup Maple Syrup
1 Orange, zested, halved, and save 1/4 Cup Orange Juice

1 Tbsp Vanilla Paste
1 Teaspoon Cinnamon
1/2 Teaspoon Ginger
1/4 Teaspoon Allspice
1/4 Teaspoon Nutmeg

2 Jumbo Eggs
1/2 Cup Heavy Whipping Cream
1/4 Cup Pecans, chopped

## Method

### Roast the potatoes

This part may be done upto 3 days in advance.

0. Preheat oven to 375°F.
1. Wash & scrub sweet potatoes. Pat dry.
2. Cut in half, across the girth. Then chop lengthwise, into at least quarters.
3. Toss in Olive Oil to coat. Then lightly dust with Chinese Five Spice.
4. Place on cookie sheet and roast for 30-45 minutes, until corners turn dark.
5. Let cool completely. Leave someolace cool overnight: microwave, empty oven, fridge, etc.
6. Peels skins off. Toss or save for a snack.
7. Slice the tender sweet potatoes across the grain, no larger than 1/2 inch cuts.
8. Put the sliced sweet potato chunks into a large container. Place in fridge until ready to use.

### Make caramel sauce

0. In a large stainless steel pot or pan, melt a stick of butter over medium-low heat.
1. Once it is completely melted, drop in a handful of fresh Sage Leaves.
2. Stir as the butter gets bubbly and starts to brown. 
3. Use a slotted spoon to remove slightly crisped Sage Leaves for garnish later.
4. Add Brown Sugar and stir until melted.
5. Add Maple Syrup, Orange Zest, Orange Juice, and spices. Stir util even.
6. Stir in Bourbon.
7. Let the alcohol burn off and thicken the sauce for a rew minutes.
8. Remove from heat.
9. Add Sweet Potato chunks and fold the sauce over them to coat.

### Make the "pie"

0. Grease a ceramic casserole dish with some butter.
1. Beat eggs and cream (and two dashes of salt) until one smooth color & texture.
2. Stir into the eggs a scoop of sauce with some potaotes.
3. Stir into the eggs another scoop of sauce and potatoes. Do not stop stirring!
4. Repeat step 3 until the egg mixture is warm.
5. Pour tempered egg mix back into the sauce and potatoes.
6. Stir until one even color with chunks of sweet potatos in it.
7. Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle the top with chopped pecans.
8. Bake at 350°F for 30 minutes, or until the pecans start to brown.

You can store this casserole in the fridge for 3 days or so. 
Return to 350°F oven for 10-15 minutes to warm before serving.
Also, once hot, top with miniature marshmallows and return to oven. 
Remove when the marshmallows brown.



